ng or int representing the ID for an image.\n    In the context of the usage of this function, this is usually used with the\n    index of the scene / image.\n\nReturns\n-------\nome_image_id: str\n    The OME standard for image IDs."]}, {"name": "bioio_ome_zarr.utils.generate_ome_channel_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "image_id", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "channel_id", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Naively generates the standard OME channel ID using a provided ID.\n\nParameters\n----------\nimage_id: str\n    An image id to pull the image specific index from.\n    See: `generate_ome_image_id` for more details.\nchannel_id: Union[str, int]\n    A string or int representing the ID for a channel.\n    In the context of the usage of this function, this is usually used with the\n    index of the channel.\n\nReturns\n-------\nome_channel_id: str\n    The OME standard for channel IDs.\n\nNotes\n-----\nImageIds are usually: \"Image:0\", \"Image:1\", or \"Image:N\",\nChannelIds are usually the combination of image index + channel index --\n\"Channel:0:0\" for the first channel of the first image for example."]}, {"name": "bioio_ome_zarr.utils.generate_ome_instrument_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "instrument_id", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project"